      "text": "1 ORDER SHEET IN THE HIGH COURT OF SINDH, BENCH AT SUKKUR. Cr.Misc.A. No.S- 538 of 2014 DATE OF HEARING ORDER WITH SIGNATURE OF HON’BLE JUDGE. 1. For Katcha Peshi. 2. For hearing of M.A 2731/2014. 23.06.2014. Mr. Qurban Ali Kalwar Adv. for applicant. Mr. A.R. Kolachi APG a/w ASI Bashir Ahmed. *************** The learned APG has filed the report submitted by the I.O. Bashir Ahmed in Crime No. 42/2014 of Police Station, Site Area Sukkur under Section 365-B PPC registered against the applicant, her husband and their relations. Per report, the statement of the applicant in terms of Section 164 Cr.P.C has been recorded wherein she has not supported the contents of FIR. The report further shows the summary for disposing of the case under ‘C’ Class has been moved to the Magistrate concerned. The Counsel for the applicant has shown his satisfaction and does not press this application as the petition has served its purpose. He requests for directions to provide necessary protection of law to the applicant and her husband may be issued. I have gone through the report of the I.O. as well as statement recorded under Section 164 Cr.P.C which shows that the applicant has not supported the contents of FIR registered, against the applicant, her husband and his relations, by the mother of the applicant. The report by the I.O. disposing of the case under ‘C’ Class in view of such statement of abductee, has been rightly submitted before the learned Magistrate concerned. Since the summary for disposal of the FIR against the applicant and her husband under ‘C’ Class has been forwarded by the police. The 2 purpose of this application, therefore, stands served which is disposed of accordingly, with directions to official respondents to provide due protection of law to the applicant."
